Three organizational culture dimensions: Innovation and risk-taking: How much a corporation rewards innovation and prudent risk-taking. Google's 20% time policy allows workers to focus on personal projects 20% of the time. Attention to detail: A company's work procedures should be precise and comprehensive. Tesla prioritizes detail in its production process to assure quality. Outcome orientation: How much a firm focuses on objectives and targets. Amazon excels at meeting performance goals and improving operations. 